        "Abstract": "Hatespeechdetectionisachallengingproblemwithmostof the datasets available in only one language: English. In this paper, we conductalargescale analysis ofmultilingualhatespeechin9languages from 16 different sources. We observe that in low resource setting, sim- ple models such as LASER embedding with logistic regression performs the best, while in high resource setting BERT based models perform better. In case of zero-shot classification, languages such as Italian and Portugueseachievegoodresults.Ourproposedframeworkcouldbeused as an efficient solution for low-resource languages. These models could also act as good baselines for future multilingual hate speech detection tasks.Wehavemadeourcodeandexperimentalsettingspublic1forother researchers."
